news.title: UK's Home REIT says two tenant firms missed payments for Nov quarter
news.para: Home REIT said Big Help Group - its largest tenant - and Noble Tree Foundation had not paid rent contractually for the quarter to Nov. 30, and the company was looking at options to obtain payment.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group faces $102 million in legal claims on bonds
news.para: The documents were lodged on Thursday and showed Oasis was the beneficial owner of $90 million worth of unsecured notes issued by Kaisa that matured in 2022.

news.title: China: Dalian Wanda Commercial Management raises $400 million in dollar bonds
news.para: The company, the property services arm of commercial property developer Dalian Wanda Group, increased the size of the deal due to strong demand from investors during the bookbuild, people familiar with the deal told Reuters.

news.title: Sebi allows virtual meetings for REITs, InVITs unitholders
news.para: Under the rules, an annual meeting of all unitholders of real estate investment trusts (REITs) and infrastructure investment trusts (InvITs) need to be held within 120 days from the end of a financial year and the time between two meetings should not exceed 15 months.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces acquires 4.25 acres land in Bengaluru
news.para: This land has residential development potential of approximately 4.6 lakh sq ft and a gross development value of approximately Rs 400 crore primarily comprising of premium residential apartments.

news.title: Haryana to enact law to give land ownership rights to villagers
news.para: “In a relief for jumla malkan, mustraka malkan, shamlat deh, jumla mustraka malkan and abadkar, pattedar, dholidar, butmidar mukrirdar and kashtkar, the Haryana government has decided to introduce a new law to give land ownership rights to them,” Haryana CM said.

news.title: The Office Pass leases 26,000 sq ft in Gurugram
news.para: The new office will come up in Unitech Cyber Park (UCP), which is close to HUDA Metro Station. This will be TOP’s fourth office in UCP with a combined capacity of over 1600 desks spread across 72,000 sq ft.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' sales booking up 28% at record Rs 716 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Kolte-Patil said it achieved sales value of Rs 1,528 crore during April-December 2022-23, a rise of 23 per cent from Rs 1,238 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Quarry owners' strike plunges over 10,000 workers in distress in Karnataka
news.para: Over 65 units have shut down their businesses, participating in the statewide protest against the state's decision to collect excess royalties. In addition, they oppose drone surveillance of their units.

news.title: About 50 acres in Aravalis to be cleared of illegal structures
news.para: On December 9, NGT had ordered the Haryana and Rajasthan governments to demolish illegal structures and restore Aravali forest land that is protected under sections 4 and 5 of the Punjab Land Protection Act (PLPA), 1900.

news.title: Property tax reminders sent to 30 government facilities in Nashik
news.para: Some of these government establishments have not paid the property tax in the past 3 to 4 years. An NMC official said there are over 30 central and state government offices that have defaulted on payment of property tax.

news.title: Berger Paints appoints Kaushik Ghosh as new CFO
news.para: The board of directors also noted the resignation of Vikash Sarda as Berger Paints' CFO.

news.title: Norms relaxed, min requirement to register plots 100 sq yards now in Gurugram
news.para: MCG commissioner PC Meena said that earlier the regularisation and sub-division was allowed for plots with a minimum area of 200 sq yards, and now it has been changed to 100 sq yards.

news.title: Mumbai: Private redevelopment of rebuilt cessed buildings may hit FSI hurdle
news.para: The Mumbai city government is working on a redevelopment plan for 454 buildings that are now old and in a very dangerous condition. These buildings were originally cessed properties, which means the government gave them to the developers to redevelop under a special program.

news.title: Telangana HC stays Ramky bid to sell plots, flats in Discovery City
news.para: Ramky and the state government through its agency, Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA), had agreed to develop nearly 750 acres in three phases into an integrated township in the area.
